00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 13=

19
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:45,000
♪Burying sorrow deep within my chest♪

20
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:49,760
♪Tonight the moon is veiled in mist♪

21
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:51,880
♪The land lies still and silent♪

22
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:57,610
♪Cold and desolate♪

23
00:01:57,640 --> 00:02:00,160
Aunt Hua, I want to go home.

24
00:02:03,190 --> 00:02:04,030
No, you can't.

25
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,390
Your exams are in a couple of days.

26
00:02:08,350 --> 00:02:09,200
I'm not taking them.

27
00:02:10,790 --> 00:02:11,630
You have to.

28
00:02:13,430 --> 00:02:14,390
Don't overthink it.

29
00:02:15,350 --> 00:02:16,520
Just go in and do your best.

30
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:19,520
I don't want commodity grain anymore.

31
00:02:20,430 --> 00:02:21,640
I want to go home.

32
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:24,560
I can't stay in the troupe anymore.

33
00:02:25,150 --> 00:02:26,350
You have to stay.

34
00:02:27,030 --> 00:02:29,000
For your uncle's sake, you can't go.

35
00:02:29,670 --> 00:02:31,000
He's not coming back.

36
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,110
Shut your mouth.

37
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,960
Say that again, and I'll rip it open.

38
00:02:38,390 --> 00:02:39,560
Your uncle is like a cat.

39
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,040
He's got nine lives.

40
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,000
Aunt Hua, I'm scared.

41
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:32,040
We've got nothing to fear.

42
00:03:51,740 --> 00:03:53,980
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

43
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,080
♪Grandma tells♪

44
00:03:57,750 --> 00:04:01,080
♪Of the brave old days♪

45
00:04:02,030 --> 00:04:11,360
♪When sacrifices were made♪

46
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:23,030
♪As it turned out♪

47
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:28,630
♪I was♪

48
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,710
Why aren't you practicing?

49
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:46,150
They say this exam cuts the bottom two.

50
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,400
Don't take it lightly.

51
00:04:48,030 --> 00:04:49,030
Leave me alone.

52
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,400
What's wrong?

53
00:04:54,360 --> 00:05:06,840
♪Through the forest,
across the snowy plains♪

54
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:15,590
♪Our spirit soars to the sky♪

55
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:20,960
♪The guard's call♪

56
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:27,280
♪Like a wolf's howl♪

57
00:05:29,910 --> 00:05:33,000
♪I step forward♪

58
00:05:35,310 --> 00:05:40,520
♪Out through the gate♪

59
00:05:40,520 --> 00:05:42,030
Stop, stop.

60
00:05:42,030 --> 00:05:44,000
What are you doing?

61
00:05:44,706 --> 00:05:46,033
Who taught you to sing like that?

62
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:47,470
Who taught you?

63
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:50,080
I've given it my all.

64
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:51,430
You wouldn't do any better.

65
00:05:52,190 --> 00:05:53,680
Move along.

66
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:57,880
You wanted him.

67
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,680
Didn't you insist on it?

68
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:03,680
You said he was the greenest grass.

69
00:06:04,070 --> 00:06:04,910
Well?

70
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:06,160
Green enough for you?

71
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:07,200
Director,

72
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:09,480
this kid is suited for the Chou role.

73
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:12,070
That's mainly spoken parts
and physical skills.

74
00:06:15,830 --> 00:06:18,190
Yi Qing'e, the teacher is calling you.

75
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:23,480
Yi Qing'e, the teacher is calling you.

76
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,870
Why aren't you going?

77
00:06:25,430 --> 00:06:26,270
What's wrong?

78
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:28,196
- Yi Qing'e!
- Hurry up.

79
00:06:28,207 --> 00:06:29,480
- Yi Qing'e!
- He's calling you.

80
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:31,870
What are you doing? You're up! Hurry!

81
00:06:32,390 --> 00:06:34,480
Yi Qing'e, what will you sing?

82
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:37,430
What are you going to sing?

83
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:39,830
Don't just stand there.

84
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:48,630
Have her sing
Grandma's Revolution Story.

85
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:53,070
Sing Grandma's Revolution Story for us.

86
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:55,030
I don't know it.

87
00:06:56,630 --> 00:06:59,430
Then sing The North Wind Blows.

88
00:06:59,430 --> 00:07:00,270
I don't know it.

89
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:02,120
The kid's just nervous.

90
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,550
She's just nervous.

91
00:07:03,570 --> 00:07:04,430
Not at her best today.

92
00:07:04,430 --> 00:07:05,800
Don't be nervous, okay?

93
00:07:06,630 --> 00:07:09,120
Just sing whatever you know.

94
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:11,190
Sing loud. Sing with confidence.

95
00:07:11,190 --> 00:07:12,680
It's okay if you mess up.

96
00:07:13,070 --> 00:07:14,430
I don't know any songs.

97
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,070
Let me say a few words.

98
00:07:20,870 --> 00:07:23,120
We all know what she's been through.

99
00:07:23,950 --> 00:07:25,920
Even adults would struggle with it.

100
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:27,360
Let alone a child.

101
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,040
I have a suggestion.

102
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,720
Let Yi Qing'e take it later.

103
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,340
I agree.

104
00:07:33,340 --> 00:07:34,220
I agree too.

105
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:35,060
Same here.

106
00:07:35,060 --> 00:07:36,000
I agree too.

107
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:44,160
That could work.

108
00:07:46,830 --> 00:07:48,630
This is outrageous.

109
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:50,070
What's so outrageous?

110
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:54,120
The exam hall is a battlefield.

111
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,560
Everyone's already in battle.

112
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:57,070
The charge has already sounded.

113
00:07:57,070 --> 00:07:58,800
And you want to charge days later?

114
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,240
Does that make any sense?

115
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,430
Why wouldn't it?

116
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,800
Good soldiers lead the charge.

117
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,089
The wounded stay in the rear.

118
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,310
If the wounded were to charge,

119
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:08,000
the commander must be an idiot.

120
00:08:08,620 --> 00:08:09,480
Look at you.

121
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,830
Hua Caixiang, don't go too far.

122
00:08:10,830 --> 00:08:12,240
Who exactly is going too far?

123
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:14,430
Forget about what Hu Sanyuan

124
00:08:14,430 --> 00:08:15,920
did for the troupe all these years.

125
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:16,806
Just take this time.

126
00:08:16,817 --> 00:08:18,070
If he won't do the stage design,

127
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:19,070
what can you do to him?

128
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:20,070
Who can condemn him?

129
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,720
Director, please sit. Sit down.

130
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:23,160
She's pregnant. Don't get mad at her.

131
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,430
Here, cool down.

132
00:08:24,430 --> 00:08:26,270
To help the troupe stage a good show,

133
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:27,720
he never complained about the work.

134
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:29,270
He did his job

135
00:08:29,270 --> 00:08:31,190
and stepped up
for what he shouldn't have.

136
00:08:31,190 --> 00:08:32,070
What happened?

137
00:08:32,630 --> 00:08:34,510
He nearly lost his life,

138
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:37,510
yet someone used it to get revenge,

139
00:08:37,510 --> 00:08:38,480
saying it was

140
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:40,680
deliberate sabotage

141
00:08:40,680 --> 00:08:42,310
and a long-term plot

142
00:08:42,310 --> 00:08:43,750
for revenge.

143
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:46,040
Can it get any more outrageous?

144
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:47,800
What is this?

145
00:08:48,070 --> 00:08:50,070
It's a frame-up! It's persecution!

146
00:08:50,070 --> 00:08:51,270
Calm down. She's pregnant.

147
00:08:51,270 --> 00:08:52,110
Don't get worked up.

148
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,320
Alright, alright.

149
00:08:56,950 --> 00:08:58,510
Hu Sanyuan is in prison.

150
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:01,270
Now, you won't even spare his kid.

151
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:04,190
Even plays aren't so vicious.

152
00:09:06,190 --> 00:09:07,390
- What's wrong?
- Alright.

153
00:09:07,390 --> 00:09:15,920
♪Grandma tells of the brave old days
when sacrifices were made♪

154
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:22,870
♪As it turned out, I was born
in the wind and raised in the rain♪

155
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:25,120
♪Oh, Grandma♪

156
00:09:25,430 --> 00:09:31,630
♪17 years of care, deep as the ocean♪

157
00:09:57,120 --> 00:10:00,000
Let her learn drums with me instead.

158
00:10:05,310 --> 00:10:06,160
Well done.

159
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:02,750
Keep it down.

160
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:27,630
I took all the Mo.

161
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,320
Where are you going?

162
00:11:45,180 --> 00:11:54,100
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

163
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,280
Who's there?

164
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:03,280
Stop right there.

165
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:11,000
Kid, where's your exit pass?

166
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:12,910
Don't run. You might fall.

167
00:12:17,500 --> 00:12:20,140
(Picket)

168
00:12:44,270 --> 00:12:45,870
Why is this truck carrying a prisoner?

169
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,360
Don't you know?

170
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:48,630
A prisoner means being shot.

171
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:51,320
So, he's to be executed?

172
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:53,200
Oh, my. He's a killer.

173
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,630
My grandma is paralyzed.

174
00:14:33,390 --> 00:14:34,720
What about your parents?

175
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,480
My dad went to work in the mountains.

176
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:40,600
He was crushed by falling rocks.

177
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:44,790
And your mom?

178
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:46,800
She lost her mind.

179
00:14:47,390 --> 00:14:48,670
She disappeared six months ago.

180
00:14:57,270 --> 00:14:58,110
Grandpa.

181
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:12,960
Here, eat.

182
00:15:13,270 --> 00:15:14,240
Eat. Here.

183
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:20,120
Have some solid food. It lasts.

184
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:39,840
White Mo.

185
00:15:55,510 --> 00:15:56,790
Grandpa, white Mo.

186
00:15:57,670 --> 00:15:58,960
Where did this Mo come from?

187
00:15:59,270 --> 00:16:00,320
That girl gave it to me.

188
00:16:01,030 --> 00:16:02,000
You eat it. Go on, eat.

189
00:16:02,270 --> 00:16:03,110
You eat.

190
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:44,000
Quick, bring me a basin.

191
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,840
Hurry, hurry. Get a basin.

192
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:46,720
Quick, quick.

193
00:16:52,480 --> 00:16:53,750
Good. Put it here.

194
00:16:56,550 --> 00:17:04,960
♪Wang Chao♪

195
00:17:08,840 --> 00:17:14,840
♪Sends word♪

196
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:20,750
What's he shouting?

197
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:22,910
It's just what he likes to sing.

198
00:17:23,630 --> 00:17:25,120
My grandpa hollers when he's bored.

199
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:28,790
He says shouting out what's bottled up

200
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:29,910
makes you feel better.

201
00:17:29,910 --> 00:17:38,200
♪Ma Han reports♪

202
00:17:41,750 --> 00:17:49,120
♪Saying♪

203
00:17:49,870 --> 00:17:57,550
♪The Princess♪

204
00:17:57,550 --> 00:18:08,440
♪Has come here♪

205
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:15,030
♪Here I am♪

206
00:18:15,550 --> 00:18:23,600
♪Stepping forward♪

207
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:32,670
♪Quickly kneeling♪

208
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,960
(What happened the night before)

209
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:27,590
(made Yi Qing'e vaguely understand)

210
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:31,240
(why people in the mountains love opera)

211
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:32,590
(and love to sing opera,)

212
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:34,960
(because it lets people)

213
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:38,400
(cry out what weighs on their hearts.)

214
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:09,520
Sis.

215
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:13,000
How did you...

216
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:15,640
Dad, Mom, Laidi's back!

217
00:21:16,030 --> 00:21:16,870
What?

218
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,160
Why are you back?

219
00:21:18,510 --> 00:21:19,696
Did you walk all the way back?

220
00:21:20,110 --> 00:21:20,950
Laidi.

221
00:21:21,830 --> 00:21:23,440
- Laidi.
- Laidi's back!

222
00:21:23,440 --> 00:21:24,350
Where did you go?

223
00:21:24,350 --> 00:21:25,240
You scared us to death.

224
00:21:25,240 --> 00:21:26,680
You really scared us.

225
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:28,550
You've got too much nerve.

226
00:21:28,550 --> 00:21:30,030
Where on earth did you run off to?

227
00:21:30,030 --> 00:21:31,510
Do you know how worried we were?

228
00:21:31,510 --> 00:21:32,350
Laidi.

229
00:21:38,350 --> 00:21:39,920
I ought to give you a good smack.

230
00:21:42,680 --> 00:21:44,830
Her uncle is such a deadbeat.

231
00:21:45,510 --> 00:21:47,110
He never took life seriously.

232
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:50,070
As a kid, he poked a hornet's nest.

233
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,880
He got stung up,

234
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:55,350
and dozens in the village got stung too.

235
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:59,000
Back then, he disliked the Director,

236
00:21:59,310 --> 00:22:01,350
so he peed in his pickle jar.

237
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:04,200
They caught him and beat him badly.

238
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:06,960
We paid him all our pickled vegetables,

239
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:09,310
so we had none to eat all winter.

240
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:12,270
- Recently,
- Thanks.

241
00:22:12,270 --> 00:22:15,270
he sent word he'd come to perform opera.

242
00:22:15,510 --> 00:22:16,440
He told us all to go.

243
00:22:16,750 --> 00:22:17,790
We were so excited

244
00:22:17,790 --> 00:22:19,640
that we nearly called the whole village.

245
00:22:20,680 --> 00:22:21,830
And what did we see?

246
00:22:23,070 --> 00:22:25,640
We were too ashamed to show our faces.

247
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:27,680
People always say

248
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,440
that the older you get,

249
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:30,920
the steadier you become.

250
00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:34,270
Why does he only cause bigger trouble?

251
00:22:34,790 --> 00:22:36,920
Now, it's turned into a serious case.

252
00:22:36,920 --> 00:22:37,880
Enough, enough.

253
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:39,350
Stop going on about that.

254
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:45,310
Here's the thing, Laidi.

255
00:22:46,270 --> 00:22:47,590
Because of your uncle,

256
00:22:48,110 --> 00:22:49,750
your exam scores,

257
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,400
and your running from the troupe,

258
00:22:51,830 --> 00:22:53,830
they are going to expel you.

259
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,640
Aunt Mi Lan, Director Glasses,

260
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:57,720
Uncle Dachui,

261
00:22:57,920 --> 00:23:00,240
and everyone else spoke up for you.

262
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:02,510
Huang Zhengjing had no choice.

263
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:05,000
Now, you're moving to the kitchen.

264
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:06,830
Aunt Mi Lan and I have talked

265
00:23:06,830 --> 00:23:07,920
with your parents.

266
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:09,680
We think the kitchen is fine.

267
00:23:10,270 --> 00:23:11,110
Right.

268
00:23:11,110 --> 00:23:13,110
You won't mix with those kids.

269
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:14,480
Back then,

270
00:23:15,110 --> 00:23:16,400
your uncle got you in

271
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:18,110
just for commodity grain, right?

272
00:23:18,110 --> 00:23:18,950
Right.

273
00:23:18,950 --> 00:23:20,960
As long as the quota stays with you,

274
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:22,200
you'll always have a meal.

275
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:23,160
Yes. Exactly.

276
00:23:25,510 --> 00:23:26,440
What are you looking at?

277
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:29,790
The teacher is right. Opera feeds you.

278
00:23:29,790 --> 00:23:31,640
Stoking the fire puts you by the pot.

279
00:23:31,960 --> 00:23:33,440
I won't learn opera.

280
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:34,960
I'll stay home, help you work,

281
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:37,000
help Mom cook, and watch my brother.

282
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:37,840
You...

283
00:23:38,350 --> 00:23:39,400
Look at you.

284
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:40,960
If you stay home,

285
00:23:41,510 --> 00:23:42,640
can your mom give you money

286
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:43,750
or grain coupons?

287
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:44,920
I have money.

288
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:51,350
I saved this myself.

289
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:52,920
Two yuan went missing.

290
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:54,110
She has so much money.

291
00:23:54,110 --> 00:23:55,200
I didn't spend a cent.

292
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:59,640
Eat up, then go with your teachers.

293
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:00,480
Do you hear me?

294
00:24:01,270 --> 00:24:02,350
I'm asking you.

295
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:06,200
I don't want to go back.
I can't take it.

296
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:07,350
What's so hard to take?

297
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:09,920
Do you know who these teachers are?

298
00:24:10,030 --> 00:24:12,000
Even our Commune Secretary
can't meet them.

299
00:24:12,110 --> 00:24:13,790
For you, they crossed mountains

300
00:24:13,790 --> 00:24:15,550
and came all the way to Jiuyangou.

301
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:17,440
Don't be so ungrateful.

302
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:18,790
Eat up and leave.

303
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,920
Stoking fires beats staying home.

304
00:24:21,229 --> 00:24:22,310
If you can't perform opera,

305
00:24:22,310 --> 00:24:23,240
you can become a chef.

306
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:25,160
That'd be something to be proud of.

307
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:26,000
Exactly.

308
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:28,350
Why are you crying?

309
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:31,070
Sir, here's the thing.

310
00:24:31,350 --> 00:24:33,400
She's been gone two days; she's tired.

311
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:34,940
She's been away from home for so long.

312
00:24:35,590 --> 00:24:37,590
How about letting her stay
for a few days?

313
00:24:40,240 --> 00:24:41,080
Is that okay?

314
00:24:41,350 --> 00:24:42,920
I'm afraid Huang Zhengjing

315
00:24:43,110 --> 00:24:44,350
may change his mind.

316
00:24:44,830 --> 00:24:46,720
Ms. Hua, this isn't up for debate.

317
00:24:47,110 --> 00:24:48,110
Take her tomorrow.

318
00:25:20,350 --> 00:25:22,000
The scenery here is beautiful.

319
00:25:23,310 --> 00:25:25,000
After so long in the troupe yard,

320
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:28,000
I forgot how wide the world is.

321
00:25:29,310 --> 00:25:30,550
A child born here takes the sky

322
00:25:30,983 --> 00:25:32,640
as their roof and the earth
as their bed.

323
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:33,960
They're used to being free.

324
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:37,550
Being locked in the troupe
is like a sheep

325
00:25:37,550 --> 00:25:38,550
getting penned up.

326
00:25:38,550 --> 00:25:39,720
It's really hard to adapt.

327
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:43,790
But people aren't sheep.

328
00:25:45,030 --> 00:25:45,870
You know?

329
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:52,160
Sis, where are our sheep?

330
00:25:52,550 --> 00:25:53,830
The state forbids keeping them,

331
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:55,880
saying we have to cut off
the tail of capitalism.

332
00:25:55,880 --> 00:25:56,750
They were taken away.

333
00:25:57,960 --> 00:25:59,240
- Taken where?
- Thanks.

334
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:00,080
The commune.

335
00:26:00,550 --> 00:26:02,160
Can we still get them back?

336
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:05,030
No way, they're mutton with Mo now.

337
00:26:05,030 --> 00:26:06,030
That's a sheep's fate.

338
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,280
Here.

339
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:08,790
Why do you get to wipe first?

340
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:10,270
Take it or leave it.

341
00:26:17,030 --> 00:26:19,240
Your uncle said
he'd take you to the troupe.

342
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:20,080
Right.

343
00:26:20,790 --> 00:26:21,880
But I never made it there.

344
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,310
Can you sing?

345
00:26:23,310 --> 00:26:24,150
Yes.

346
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:25,790
Sing something for me.

347
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:35,640
♪Sing a folk song to the Party♪

348
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:42,200
♪I compare the Party to my mother♪

349
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:43,280
Aunt Hua,

350
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:44,550
my sister sings really well.

351
00:26:44,550 --> 00:26:45,920
Please talk to my dad again.

352
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:47,270
Take my sister to the troupe.

353
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:48,480
Can you?

354
00:26:49,030 --> 00:26:49,870
No.

355
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:51,960
It can't be changed now.

356
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:56,000
Your sister sings on pitch.

357
00:26:57,720 --> 00:27:01,510
Your voice is fuller, more grounded.

358
00:27:09,830 --> 00:27:10,720
Mom's calling you.

359
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:18,920
Actually, Laidi

360
00:27:18,920 --> 00:27:20,750
isn't tone-deaf by nature.

361
00:27:21,590 --> 00:27:23,790
She lacks confidence and technique.

362
00:27:23,790 --> 00:27:25,030
She can still change.

363
00:27:25,550 --> 00:27:27,550
Plus, she doesn't even sing properly.

364
00:27:29,750 --> 00:27:31,070
I'll leave her to you from now on.

365
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:33,550
Why do you never give me the good ones?

366
00:27:41,640 --> 00:27:42,680
Over the years,

367
00:27:44,110 --> 00:27:45,680
I've let you down in many ways.

368
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:48,240
I'm sorry.

369
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:52,720
I'm sorry too.

370
00:27:55,510 --> 00:27:57,160
I wrote the letter

371
00:27:57,640 --> 00:27:58,686
to Huang Zhengjing's wife.

372
00:27:59,440 --> 00:28:00,400
I figured.

373
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:05,000
I've been wondering:

374
00:28:07,070 --> 00:28:08,720
Do you really love opera that much?

375
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:10,440
Always fighting with me.

376
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:13,790
Writing that letter
and fighting with you

377
00:28:13,790 --> 00:28:14,960
are two different things.

378
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:18,310
Besides, am I fighting for opera?

379
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:21,000
You fought me over a man?

380
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:22,350
What we fight over doesn't matter.

381
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:24,830
What matters is
that it's you I'm fighting.

382
00:28:26,550 --> 00:28:27,680
Are you out of your mind?

383
00:28:27,786 --> 00:28:28,830
What did I ever do to you?

384
00:28:28,830 --> 00:28:30,270
Why can't you stand seeing me happy?

385
00:28:30,880 --> 00:28:32,160
I want you to be happy.

386
00:28:32,750 --> 00:28:34,350
Just not happier than me.

387
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:38,110
Then I must be happier than you.

388
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:39,830
I'm going to be a mom.

389
00:28:48,400 --> 00:28:49,550
As long as you're happy.

390
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:04,550
Yi Qing'e is back.

391
00:29:07,070 --> 00:29:07,910
That smell.

392
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:10,110
How did Yi Qing'e come back?

393
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:11,630
Yeah.

394
00:29:12,110 --> 00:29:13,830
Where did Ms. Hua find her?

395
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:15,080
Exactly.

396
00:29:15,091 --> 00:29:16,040
Where did she come from?

397
00:29:16,040 --> 00:29:16,880
Come with me.

398
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:18,200
Right. Where did she go?

399
00:29:19,790 --> 00:29:20,630
Exactly.

400
00:29:27,750 --> 00:29:28,590
Master Qiu.

401
00:29:28,790 --> 00:29:29,630
Master Song.

402
00:29:29,880 --> 00:29:30,720
The kid is here.

403
00:29:31,550 --> 00:29:32,390
Here she is.

404
00:29:34,110 --> 00:29:36,350
No need to introduce her, right?

405
00:29:36,350 --> 00:29:38,240
Transferred from the trainee class.

406
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:39,590
Here to help us.

407
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:41,880
From now on, she's one of us.

408
00:29:41,880 --> 00:29:42,880
We're short on hands.

409
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:44,750
I asked for help, and this is it?

410
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:46,920
Isn't the kid a person?

411
00:29:47,350 --> 00:29:48,510
What can she do?

412
00:29:48,640 --> 00:29:49,880
Like a green walnut.

413
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:52,310
I can't peel it or eat it.

414
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:53,940
Who are you trying to fool?

415
00:29:57,920 --> 00:29:59,200
She can't handle heavy work.

416
00:29:59,550 --> 00:30:01,030
But she can lend a hand.

417
00:30:01,350 --> 00:30:02,680
She can peel onions and garlic

418
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:05,110
and tend the fire.

419
00:30:05,110 --> 00:30:05,886
Right.

420
00:30:05,897 --> 00:30:07,240
Welcome to the cooking squad, kid.

421
00:30:07,240 --> 00:30:08,680
Good. Welcome, welcome.

422
00:30:10,070 --> 00:30:10,910
Kid,

423
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:14,030
Master Song is your teacher now.

424
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:17,350
Master Liao is new,
but he's your master too.

425
00:30:18,310 --> 00:30:21,510
From now on, speak sweetly, stay sharp.

426
00:30:21,510 --> 00:30:23,640
Be quick with your hands,
busy on your feet.

427
00:30:24,240 --> 00:30:25,080
Got that?

428
00:30:25,270 --> 00:30:26,110
Good.

429
00:30:26,510 --> 00:30:29,680
Come, kiddo. Opera has costume gear.

430
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:31,920
Physical skills practice has gear too.

431
00:30:32,510 --> 00:30:33,590
So, we also have gear.

432
00:30:34,030 --> 00:30:35,590
We knew you were coming.

433
00:30:35,590 --> 00:30:37,720
So, we prepared a set for you.

434
00:30:38,750 --> 00:30:39,920
Your hand.

435
00:30:42,550 --> 00:30:43,390
Good.

436
00:30:44,030 --> 00:30:44,870
Look.

437
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:47,070
Let's see how it fits.

438
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:50,550
Come on, let Aunt Hua have a look.

439
00:30:56,830 --> 00:30:57,670
You look great.

440
00:31:05,790 --> 00:31:06,630
Laidi,

441
00:31:07,350 --> 00:31:09,310
after sweeping,
remember to feed the pigs.

442
00:31:09,550 --> 00:31:10,680
Sleep early when you're done.

443
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:12,240
I'm heading out.

444
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,426
Don't forget to turn off the lights.

445
00:31:15,750 --> 00:31:16,960
Five-five seven.

446
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:20,070
Five-eight, five-nine, sixty-one.

447
00:31:20,070 --> 00:31:22,790
Six-five six, six-five seven.

448
00:31:22,790 --> 00:31:25,830
Six-eight, six-nine, seventy-one.

449
00:31:25,830 --> 00:31:28,830
Seven-five six, seven-five seven.

450
00:31:28,830 --> 00:31:31,720
Seven-eight, seven-nine, eighty-one.

451
00:31:31,720 --> 00:31:34,510
Eight-five six, eight-five seven.

452
00:31:34,510 --> 00:31:37,310
Eight-eight, eight-nine, ninety-one.

453
00:31:37,310 --> 00:31:38,150
Nine-five...

454
00:32:02,860 --> 00:32:07,140
(Keep things clean)

455
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:08,070
I'm heading out.

456
00:32:08,070 --> 00:32:08,920
Feng Xiaoxiao.

457
00:32:08,920 --> 00:32:09,880
Wait for me.

458
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:12,110
I waited for you last time.

459
00:32:13,920 --> 00:32:14,760
I'll help you.

460
00:32:15,260 --> 00:32:16,110
No need.

461
00:32:16,110 --> 00:32:17,000
It's fine.

462
00:32:18,790 --> 00:32:20,110
You're even feeding pigs now?

463
00:32:20,550 --> 00:32:21,590
Yi Qing'e,

464
00:32:21,590 --> 00:32:23,400
when will that pig be fat enough?

465
00:32:24,110 --> 00:32:25,720
I'll butcher you. Move.

466
00:32:26,350 --> 00:32:28,200
Does your pig eat crap?

467
00:32:28,200 --> 00:32:30,590
Come on, why are you so gross?

468
00:32:31,510 --> 00:32:32,830
I'm warning you.

469
00:32:32,830 --> 00:32:34,030
Warning? Who are you warning?

470
00:32:34,030 --> 00:32:34,880
Ow, ow, ow!

471
00:32:35,310 --> 00:32:36,240
Go easy!

472
00:32:36,240 --> 00:32:37,080
Let go!

473
00:32:37,350 --> 00:32:38,720
Let go, let go!

474
00:32:38,740 --> 00:32:39,600
Shut up.

475
00:32:39,610 --> 00:32:40,750
Let go! It hurts!

476
00:32:40,750 --> 00:32:41,590
My hand! My fingers!

477
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:42,790
My fingers, my fingers!

478
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:45,160
It hurts! It hurts!

479
00:32:50,200 --> 00:32:51,680
Bang, bang!

480
00:32:56,230 --> 00:32:57,070
Come on, guess.

481
00:32:57,070 --> 00:32:58,463
Rock-paper-scissors.

482
00:32:58,510 --> 00:33:00,000
Rock-paper-scissors.

483
00:33:01,400 --> 00:33:02,240
Missed.

484
00:33:03,640 --> 00:33:04,830
Rock-paper-scissors.

485
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:06,520
You again?

486
00:33:08,110 --> 00:33:08,950
I'll go first.

487
00:33:11,550 --> 00:33:14,510
Lights out again. What rotten luck.

488
00:33:16,350 --> 00:33:17,550
Such a jinx.

489
00:33:18,110 --> 00:33:19,880
What's that smell? It reeks.

490
00:33:19,880 --> 00:33:23,070
What else? Slop, of course.

491
00:33:23,070 --> 00:33:24,200
It stinks.

492
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:25,240
Like a pigsty.

493
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:26,080
Yi Qing'e,

494
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:27,880
you're with the kitchen now.

495
00:33:27,920 --> 00:33:29,070
So, you're not under me.

496
00:33:29,550 --> 00:33:30,920
But this dorm is my turf.

497
00:33:31,550 --> 00:33:33,000
Take your clothes out

498
00:33:33,546 --> 00:33:34,750
and wash off that pigsty smell

499
00:33:34,750 --> 00:33:36,070
before you come back in.

500
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:37,830
Move it.

501
00:33:37,830 --> 00:33:38,830
Hurry up and go.

502
00:33:38,830 --> 00:33:40,750
Why are you spacing out? Go.

503
00:33:40,750 --> 00:33:41,680
Hurry up, go.

504
00:33:41,680 --> 00:33:42,590
Go on.

505
00:33:42,590 --> 00:33:43,440
Hurry up and go.

506
00:33:43,440 --> 00:33:44,680
Go wash up.

507
00:33:44,830 --> 00:33:45,830
Get out.

508
00:33:46,440 --> 00:33:47,790
Close the door behind you.

509
00:34:03,350 --> 00:34:04,200
Laidi.

510
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:06,590
Bring over the washed vegetables.

511
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:14,440
Laidi, Laidi.

512
00:34:14,440 --> 00:34:16,160
Quick, get a basin of water.

513
00:34:16,160 --> 00:34:17,440
The corn gruel is too thick.

514
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:18,280
Laidi.

515
00:34:18,830 --> 00:34:19,680
Come here. Come on.

516
00:34:19,680 --> 00:34:21,200
- Come on.
- Come, come.

517
00:34:21,200 --> 00:34:22,240
Okay, okay.

518
00:34:24,720 --> 00:34:26,790
Go add some water for me.

519
00:34:28,920 --> 00:34:29,760
Laidi.

520
00:34:30,590 --> 00:34:32,270
Add two shovels of coal for us.

521
00:34:32,270 --> 00:34:33,680
The fire's weak. Stoke it up.

522
00:34:33,680 --> 00:34:34,520
Hurry up!

523
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:46,200
Okay, my kid.

524
00:34:46,830 --> 00:34:48,310
You can't keep adding coal.

525
00:34:48,640 --> 00:34:49,480
You can't...

526
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:51,500
It's only making smoke now.

527
00:34:58,680 --> 00:34:59,520
Hurry!

528
00:35:00,160 --> 00:35:01,920
Stop dawdling! Hurry!

529
00:35:02,700 --> 00:35:03,560
Attention!

530
00:35:03,570 --> 00:35:04,920
Right face!

531
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:06,160
Double time, march!

532
00:35:06,270 --> 00:35:10,640
One, two, one! One, two, one!

533
00:35:10,640 --> 00:35:11,880
Keep your distance!

534
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:14,720
Plead guilty and accept reform.

535
00:35:14,720 --> 00:35:17,510
Follow the rules for an early release.

536
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:27,200
Eat up! Eat up!

537
00:35:27,590 --> 00:35:32,310
Hoeing fields under the midday sun.

538
00:35:32,310 --> 00:35:36,510
Every grain comes from hard work.

539
00:35:58,260 --> 00:36:04,700
(Turn over a new leaf)

540
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:25,320
What is this?

541
00:36:27,190 --> 00:36:28,230
The stitches are crooked.

542
00:36:28,230 --> 00:36:29,416
Are you sewing pig intestines?

543
00:36:31,110 --> 00:36:32,409
Can you keep the stitch straight?

544
00:36:33,590 --> 00:36:34,430
Take it apart.

545
00:36:34,920 --> 00:36:35,760
Sew it again.

546
00:36:45,110 --> 00:36:45,950
Hu Sanyuan.

547
00:36:46,510 --> 00:36:47,350
Here.

548
00:36:48,190 --> 00:36:49,030
Come with me.

549
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:01,630
The correctional officer said

550
00:37:02,630 --> 00:37:04,230
you're like you've gone mute now.

551
00:37:05,800 --> 00:37:07,440
You don't talk all day.

552
00:37:09,510 --> 00:37:11,150
The blast must've left you dazed.

553
00:37:12,510 --> 00:37:13,710
A blast that big

554
00:37:15,590 --> 00:37:17,280
takes time to recover from.

555
00:37:19,110 --> 00:37:20,840
I don't talk much now either.

556
00:37:23,230 --> 00:37:24,510
I just want to be alone

557
00:37:25,760 --> 00:37:26,960
and sit quietly.

558
00:37:28,840 --> 00:37:31,760
Before coming, I visited Nail.

559
00:37:32,920 --> 00:37:34,186
I burned paper offerings for him

560
00:37:35,670 --> 00:37:37,123
and told him I was coming to see you.

561
00:37:38,190 --> 00:37:39,400
I also told him

562
00:37:40,760 --> 00:37:41,920
you survived.

563
00:37:44,150 --> 00:37:46,230
This is heaven's punishment for you.

564
00:37:47,670 --> 00:37:48,960
It wants you to pay for life.

565
00:37:53,510 --> 00:37:55,440
Heaven wants me to pay for life too.

566
00:37:57,710 --> 00:37:59,230
I've sung opera half my life.

567
00:38:01,440 --> 00:38:02,400
Onstage,

568
00:38:03,550 --> 00:38:05,710
we worked together like magic.

569
00:38:07,070 --> 00:38:07,960
Offstage,

570
00:38:10,070 --> 00:38:11,510
we both lost our tune.

571
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,190
I'm leaving

572
00:38:18,550 --> 00:38:19,800
for another place

573
00:38:20,590 --> 00:38:22,070
and singing another story.

574
00:38:25,590 --> 00:38:27,190
Let's both take care from here.

575
00:38:29,190 --> 00:38:30,440
For the scenes still to come,

576
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:32,840
sing them well.

577
00:38:40,230 --> 00:38:41,070
And Laidi...

578
00:38:43,670 --> 00:38:44,550
Laidi

579
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:47,190
got dragged into this.

580
00:38:48,400 --> 00:38:50,320
She left the trainee class
for the kitchen.

581
00:38:51,510 --> 00:38:53,030
But I think that's for the best.

582
00:38:54,230 --> 00:38:56,760
There's still a chance.

583
00:38:57,440 --> 00:38:58,840
If she stays with the troupe,

584
00:38:59,440 --> 00:39:01,110
she'll get another shot.

585
00:39:04,070 --> 00:39:05,280
She's in the kitchen.

586
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:07,800
Then we can both relax.

587
00:39:10,110 --> 00:39:12,070
Qiu Cunyi and Master Song

588
00:39:13,230 --> 00:39:15,000
won't leave her with no one.

589
00:39:19,280 --> 00:39:21,510
Tell her to keep practicing.

590
00:39:22,630 --> 00:39:24,000
She promised me.

591
00:39:27,110 --> 00:39:28,550
Then you promise me too.

592
00:39:30,710 --> 00:39:31,960
Don't give up.

593
00:39:33,630 --> 00:39:34,840
For all the shows ahead,

594
00:39:36,150 --> 00:39:37,000
sing them well.

595
00:40:26,630 --> 00:40:27,800
What do you need?

596
00:40:28,230 --> 00:40:30,480
Always stewed cabbage
with tofu and vermicelli.

597
00:40:30,710 --> 00:40:31,583
How can it taste good?

598
00:40:32,730 --> 00:40:35,360
We make a tub; half goes to the pigs.

599
00:40:35,537 --> 00:40:37,270
Without meat and oil,
how could it be good?

600
00:40:37,920 --> 00:40:39,550
You don't know costs
till you run things.

601
00:40:39,550 --> 00:40:40,800
Easy for you to say.

602
00:40:41,040 --> 00:40:41,990
Your skills are off.

603
00:40:41,990 --> 00:40:43,510
Don't blame anything else.

604
00:40:44,440 --> 00:40:46,800
Listen, I've put up
with you for a long time.

605
00:40:46,811 --> 00:40:48,110
You even turned shredded potatoes

606
00:40:48,110 --> 00:40:49,160
into potato sticks.

607
00:40:49,160 --> 00:40:51,070
Big pot dishes
don't need cuts that thin.

608
00:40:51,070 --> 00:40:52,190
They'd just turn to mush.

609
00:40:52,190 --> 00:40:54,110
I see. It's not your knife skills.

610
00:40:54,110 --> 00:40:55,510
It's you who's off.

611
00:40:55,510 --> 00:40:57,230
It's nice out there. Go wait outside.

612
00:40:57,480 --> 00:40:59,320
If you're not helping, why talk so much?

613
00:41:00,550 --> 00:41:01,710
I'm helping you?

614
00:41:02,030 --> 00:41:03,360
At your level,

615
00:41:03,360 --> 00:41:05,670
even I couldn't help.

616
00:41:14,150 --> 00:41:15,030
Idiot.

617
00:41:16,230 --> 00:41:18,760
You need to pull apart
the spinach roots.

618
00:41:18,760 --> 00:41:20,030
Wash off all the dirt.

619
00:41:20,400 --> 00:41:22,440
Clean the carrot roots too.

620
00:41:22,440 --> 00:41:23,510
Is the water cold?

621
00:41:23,510 --> 00:41:24,350
No, it's not.

622
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:28,800
Laidi.

623
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:30,160
Are you tired?

624
00:41:30,510 --> 00:41:31,350
No.

625
00:41:31,550 --> 00:41:32,880
What's your full name?

626
00:41:33,510 --> 00:41:34,550
Yi Qing'e.

627
00:41:35,030 --> 00:41:36,110
Which Yi is that?

628
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:37,440
The Yi from "easy".

629
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:40,190
Rare surname. Hard to remember.

630
00:41:40,550 --> 00:41:42,000
Then I'll call you Qing'e.

631
00:41:45,630 --> 00:41:47,330
Always honking away.

632
00:41:47,341 --> 00:41:49,579
The best are opera singers;
next are pimps and pushers.

633
00:41:49,590 --> 00:41:51,643
Lower still are cuckolds,
and lowest are tortoises.

634
00:41:51,800 --> 00:41:54,760
Those were the old lower nine trades.

635
00:41:54,760 --> 00:41:55,600
You know that?

636
00:41:55,760 --> 00:41:58,190
Chefs outranked opera performers.

637
00:41:58,190 --> 00:41:59,590
Listen to you.

638
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:02,110
We still make our living off them.

639
00:42:02,180 --> 00:42:03,200
Oh, come on.

640
00:42:03,670 --> 00:42:05,400
You always have to butt in.

641
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:09,360
Qing'e, do you know what I used to do?

642
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:11,880
Master Liao is from Chang'an Restaurant.

643
00:42:14,020 --> 00:42:18,480
Top-class place in Qinchuan.

644
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:20,800
Only big shots get to eat there.

645
00:42:21,510 --> 00:42:23,760
I cook for people with status.

646
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:25,510
They always pick on me.

647
00:42:26,550 --> 00:42:28,440
They learned in the army cooking squad.

648
00:42:28,440 --> 00:42:30,030
They only know big pot dishes.

649
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:34,030
Qing'e, I'll teach you stir-fry.

650
00:42:34,410 --> 00:42:35,710
Do you know what it means?

651
00:42:36,840 --> 00:42:38,920
One wok, one plate. That's it.

652
00:42:40,150 --> 00:42:42,480
Every farm home does that.

653
00:42:42,480 --> 00:42:43,320
Give it a rest.

654
00:42:43,800 --> 00:42:45,920
Can they make sautéed pork slices,
Guo Bao Rou,

655
00:42:45,920 --> 00:42:47,190
or chicken stew with mushrooms?

656
00:42:47,510 --> 00:42:49,480
They've never even heard of them.

657
00:42:50,110 --> 00:42:52,670
Do you know why that stew
uses young chicken?

658
00:42:53,043 --> 00:42:54,360
Because young chicken is tender.

659
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:55,200
Laidi.

660
00:42:55,510 --> 00:42:56,400
Go down there.

661
00:42:56,630 --> 00:42:57,920
Bring me a basket of potatoes.

662
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

663
00:43:08,840 --> 00:43:09,840
Many other troupes

664
00:43:09,840 --> 00:43:11,440
have started restaging the old plays.

665
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:13,190
These kids can't be trained like this.

666
00:43:13,190 --> 00:43:14,360
This fancy posturing is

667
00:43:14,360 --> 00:43:15,840
not even good enough to be walk-ons.

668
00:43:15,840 --> 00:43:17,190
Acting is about endurance.

669
00:43:17,190 --> 00:43:18,590
Endure the pain in your body

670
00:43:18,590 --> 00:43:20,000
and the bitterness in your heart.

671
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:21,510
As long as you're willing to suffer

672
00:43:21,510 --> 00:43:22,436
and do as I say,

673
00:43:22,447 --> 00:43:24,510
I promise you'll make a name
for yourself in opera.

674
00:43:24,510 --> 00:43:25,710
I have a favor to ask you.

675
00:43:25,710 --> 00:43:27,110
Practice hard during the day;

676
00:43:27,110 --> 00:43:28,630
at night, you come back and teach me.

677
00:43:28,630 --> 00:43:30,800
Laidi, one more flip for you.

678
00:43:31,780 --> 00:43:32,630
Heiwa!

679
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

680
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

681
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

682
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

683
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

684
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

685
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

686
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

687
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

688
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

689
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

690
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

691
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

692
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

693
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

694
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

695
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

696
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

697
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

698
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

699
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪

